title: Skateboarding Club Meeting
description: Minutes of the Skateboarding Club meeting held in Shafer Hall Room 221.

title: Acceptance of Previous Minutes
description: Motion to accept the minutes from the meeting on September 12, 2006.
conclusion: Motion carries with 7 in favor, 0 opposed, 1 abstention.

title: President's Report
description: Constitution finalized and will be submitted to advisor. Distribution of first aid kits planned for April 12, 2006. Kim offered to drive the van.

title: Vice President's Report
description: DJ SK8 available for Skate-a-Palooza on May 18, 2007. Services will include sound system, lights, and various entertainment for $600.
conclusion: Motion carries with 6 in favor, 1 opposed, 1 abstention.

title: Treasurer's Report
description: Budget and fundraising account balances were discussed. Awaiting invoice from Boards ‘R’ Us.

title: Old Business
description: Event registration for Skateboard Workshop approved. Room reservation for April 20th needs submission. Discussion on NY trip expenses including hotel and meal allowances.
conclusion: Motion carries to allocate $1,010 for hotel and $20 for parking for the NY trip.

title: New Business
description: Nominations for executive board positions to be held in two weeks, with elections following week.

title: Announcements
description: West Indian Society's Patty Sale on Monday and President's Inauguration on April 13th.

title: Adjournment
conclusion: Motion carries with 8 in favor, 0 opposed, 0 abstentions.
